column1: #Text=is a city in the Trans-Pecos region of Texas .
#Text=I-10 east of Van Horn and west of Ozona .
#Text=US 385 north of Marathon and south of Odessa .
#Text=It is an excellent example of Territorial Architecture built of adobe with Victorian wood trim , and houses exhibits on area history .
#Text=The pavilion was built in 1938 over the Big Chief Spring .
#Text=It was the largest spring in the system and flowed 65 million gallons of water a day .
#Text=Built in the 1880s , was once owned by A.J. Royal .
#Text=Built in 1858 and used until 1886 , the fort was home to many troops of buffalo soldiers during the height of the Indian menace .
#Text=Guardhouse , Officers ' Row , and Parade Grounds ; a museum is housed in the enlisted men 's barracks and a visitor 's center is located at 301 E. Third .
#Text=Also served as a bank and saloon , it was built in 1878 .
#Text=The second floor was added in the 1930s as a WPA project .
#Text=It now serves as the Small Community Hall .
#Text=Across the street is one of the nine springs in the Comanche Springs system .
#Text=This one is named the Blue Hole .
#Text=Where only a very few markers show anyone over the age of 40 , a testimony to the hard frontier life .
#Text=Pecos County 's original jail was built in 1883 .
#Text=Built in the 1896 , was one of the first Protestant churches west of the Pecos River .
